        "Model Reasoning": "To calculate the annual 1% parametric VaR using the data in Exhibit 2, we can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Identify the Inputs**:\n   - Average return: 0.026% per day\n   - Standard deviation: 0.501% per day\n   - Portfolio value: CAD 260 million\n\n2. **Convert Daily Standard Deviation to Annual**:\n   - Assuming 252 trading days in a year, the annual standard deviation is:\n     $\n     \\text{Annual standard deviation} = 0.501\\% \\times \\sqrt{252}\n     $\n\n3. **Calculate the Z-Score for 1% VaR**:\n   - The Z-score for a 1% VaR (one-tailed) is approximately 2.33.\n\n4. **Calculate the Annual VaR**:\n   - The formula for VaR is:\n     $\n     \\text{VaR} = \\text{Portfolio Value} \\times (\\text{Z-score} \\times \\text{Annual Standard Deviation})\n     $\n   - Plug in the values:\n     $\n     \\text{VaR} = 260,000,000 \\times (2.33 \\times 0.501\\% \\times \\sqrt{252})\n     $\n\n5. **Compute the Result**:\n   - Calculate the annual standard deviation:\n     $\n     \\text{Annual standard deviation} = 0.501\\% \\times \\sqrt{252} \\approx 7.95\\%\n     $\n   - Calculate the VaR:\n     $\n     \\text{VaR} = 260,000,000 \\times (2.33 \\times 7.95\\%) \\approx 260,000,000 \\times 0.1853 \\approx CAD 48 million\n     $\n\nTherefore, the correct option is 【C】.",
